         <abstract id="aspace_987fcaf602a85fc2898d171ced5e9233">Correspondence between Reuben L. and Marcionella V. Curtiss during World War II when each was serving in the United States Army make up the bulk of the papers. Reuben L. Curtiss's letters are sent from various parts of the United States, Africa, India, and China. Marcionella V. Curtiss's letters reflect her service in Australia, New Guinea and the Philippine Islands. There is also a diary kept by Reuben L. Curtiss (1944-1945), and a biographical sketch written by Marcionella V. Curtiss in 1979.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname source="local">
               <part>Curtiss, Reuben Lucius, 1897-1978</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
